author: deedubbu
msg: Updating Contacts API to match the June 16th W3C Spec.
The June 16th 2011 update to the W3C Contacts API contains the
following changes:
- Remove ContactError.NOT_FOUND_ERROR.  Move other values up.
- Add pref and type members to ContactAddress.
- Add pref and type members to ContactOrganization.
- Remove revision, gender and timezone members from Contact.
- Modify Contact.save to return contact object with full set of
properties.
- Return ContactError.UNKNOWN_ERROR from Contact.remove when contact
does not exist.
- Set false as default for ContactFindOptions multiple member.
- Remove updatedSince member from ContactFindOptions.
- Move contacts from navigator.service.contacts to navigator.contacts
- Throw TypeError in navigator.contacts.find if success callback not
specified.
- Return ContactError.INVALID_ARGUMENT_ERROR from navigator.contacts.find
if fields argument not specified.
